pects financially through credit reports, bank statements, etc. Reviewing occupancy as it relates to staffing Assisting in the hiring and recruitment processes Handling all resident and family grievances JOB REQUIREMENTS Requirements: Bachelor\u2019s degree; Degree in Healthcare Administration, Hospitality Management, or Business preferred 3-5 years of management or healthcare related experience Having assumed a managerial role that was responsible for multiple disciplines Possessing budgeting and staffing experience Proficiency with Windows applications such as Excel and Outlook Ability to lift a minimum of 50 pounds Benefits As an Executive Director for Benchmark Senior Living, you will have the opportunity to improve the quality of life of the Senior Citizens living in your community. While the position has its challenges, it is also highly rewarding and gratifying. Furthermore, Benchmark offers ample advancement opportunities for top performers as well as excellent compensation and benefits. "
